Package actr.model

Class Summary
Audio The audio module representing ACT-R's auditory perception.
Bold Prediction of BOLD response that arises from buffer activity.
Buffers Maintains the state of the ACT-R buffers.
Chunk Chunks of declarative knowledge represented as pairings of slots and slot values.
Declarative Declarative memory that holds chunks of declarative knowledge.
Event The abstract class for a model event.
Events A queue of upcoming events sorted by time.
ExtendedMemory External declarative memory that can be used to supplement the Java standard memory implementation (e.g., an external database).
Imaginal The imaginal module that holds a temporary problem state for the current task.
Instantiation An instantiation of a production rule specified as a mapping from variables to values.
Model The highest-level class representing an ACT-R model.
Module Abstract class for an ACT-R module.
Motor The motor module representing ACT-R's manual movements.
ParseError  
Procedural Procedural memory that holds skill knowledge represented as production rules.
Production Condition-action production rules that serve as the primary representation of cognitive skill.
Speech The speech module representing ACT-R's vocal speech generation.
Symbol A symbol within the system, roughly represented as a string but allowing "==" as a fast test for equality.
Temporal The temporal module representing ACT-R's perception of time.
Utilities Utility code with various utility variables and methods.
Vision The vision module representing ACT-R's visual perception.
